{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-2050","published":"2022-11-11T11:04:31Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:18:31.334162Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-41974"],"summary":"multipath-tools security update","details":"This package provides the multipath tool and the multipathd daemon to manage dm-multipath devices. multipath can detect and set up multipath maps. multipathd sets up multipath maps automatically, monitors path devices for failure, removal, or addition, and applies the necessary changes to the multipath maps to ensure continuous availability of the map devices.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nmultipath-tools 0.7.0 through 0.9.x before 0.9.2 allows local users to obtain root access, as exploited alone or in conjunction with CVE-2022-41973. Local users able to write to UNIX domain sockets can bypass access controls and manipulate the multipath setup. This can lead to local privilege escalation to root. This occurs because an attacker can repeat a keyword, which is mishandled because arithmetic ADD is used instead of bitwise OR.(CVE-2022-41974)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"multipath-tools","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/multipath-tools&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"0.8.4-17.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["kpartx-0.8.4-17.oe1.aarch64.rpm","multipath-tools-debugsource-0.8.4-17.oe1.aarch64.rpm","multipath-tools-help-0.8.4-17.oe1.aarch64.rpm","multipath-tools-0.8.4-17.oe1.aarch64.rpm","multipath-tools-debuginfo-0.8.4-17.oe1.aarch64.rpm","multipath-tools-devel-0.8.4-17.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["multipath-tools-0.8.4-17.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["multipath-tools-debuginfo-0.8.4-17.oe1.x86_64.rpm","multipath-tools-debugsource-0.8.4-17.oe1.x86_64.rpm","multipath-tools-help-0.8.4-17.oe1.x86_64.rpm","multipath-tools-0.8.4-17.oe1.x86_64.rpm","multipath-tools-devel-0.8.4-17.oe1.x86_64.rpm","kpartx-0.8.4-17.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https: